The paper deals with the evaluation of routing protocols in mobile ad-hoc networks and vehicular ad-hoc networks, which are both subfields of networked systems and technologies. The paper also discusses the modification of default parameters of the selected protocols, which falls under the category of network optimization and control. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other possible sub-categories include cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these subfields are also relevant to the study of mobile ad-hoc networks and routing protocols.
